<HEADLINE>
ACTING KMT HEAD TERMS UNITY KEY FACTOR FOR KMT CHAIRMANSHIP BID
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,  March 5 (CNA) 03/05/07  19:19:16 (By Luis Huang)
</P>
<P>
Main opposition Kuomintang (KMT) Acting Chairman Wu Poh-hsiung
said Monday that unity among party members will be a key factor
he will take into account when considering the question of
whether or not to run for the KMT chairmanship.
</P>
<P>
Describing the chairmanship as an "unpleasant task" during a news
conference held at the KMT headquarters, Wu said that if his
running for the post will help reinforce party solidarity, he
will be willing to take part in the party's chairmanship by-
election slated for April 7.
</P>
<P>
Asked when KMT Honorary Chairman Lien Chan, former KMT Chairman
Ma Ying-jeou, Legislative Yuan Speaker Wang Jin-pyng and he will
hold a second meeting to discuss how best to decide the KMT
presidential ticket, Wu said no date has been set, but that he
has always maintained smooth communications with Lien.
</P>
<P>
The by-election was made necessary by Ma's resignation as KMT
chairman Feb. 13 immediately after he was indicted on corruption
charges for his alleged misuse of a special allowance fund for
his discretionary use during his two terms as Taipei mayor from
1998 - 2006. Ma simultaneously announced that he will run in the
2008 presidential election.
</P>
<P>
Wang, a KMT stalwart, is also widely considered a potential
contender for the 2008 presidential  race,  has not announced a
presidential bid.
</P>
<P>
The KMT leadership has voiced the hope that Lien will mediate
among the party's presidential aspirants to help ensure that the
party fields only one presidential candidate.
</P>
